<DOC><DOCNO> AP890213-0081 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-13-89 1334EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--SoldierKilled     02-13 0174</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Soldier Killed,0178</SECOND><HEAD>Norwegian Soldier Killed, Comrade Injured in Car Accident</HEAD><DATELINE>TYRE, Lebanon (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An armored personnel carrier skidded off theroad in southeast Lebanon on Monday, killing a Norwegian soldier ofthe U.N. peacekeeping force and injuring another, a U.N. spokesmansaid.   The accident occurred near the town of Rashaya in the foothillsof Mount Hermon, two miles north of Israel's self-designatedsecurity zone in south Lebanon, said spokesman Timur Goksel.   ``One Norwegian private was killed and another was wounded. Threeother Norwegians in the APC escaped unharmed,'' said Goksel,declining to identify the victims.   Goksel said both were flown to the Lebanese border town ofNaqoura, which houses the command headquarters of the U.N. InterimForce in Lebanon.   The accident brought U.N. fatalities to 159 since the5,844-strong force was deployed in south Lebanon in 1978 to serve asa buffer between Israel and Palestinian guerrillas. Among thosekilled were 16 Norwegians.   The force is made up of troops from France, Fiji, Finland, Ghana,Ireland, Italy, Nepal, Norway and Sweden.</TEXT></DOC>